def count_Substrings(s):
    n = len(s)
    count,sum = 0,0
    mp = defaultdict(lambda : 0)
    mp[0] += 1
    for i in range(n):
        sum += ord(s[i]) - ord('0')
        count += mp[sum - (i + 1)]
        mp[sum - (i + 1)] += 1
    return count

def get_median(arr1, arr2, n):

  j = 0
  m1 = -1
  m2 = -1
  count = 0
  while count < n + 1:
    count += 1
    if i == n:
      m1 = m2
      m2 = arr2[0]
      break
    elif j == n:
      m1 = m2
      m2 = arr1[0]
      break
    if arr1[i] <= arr2[j]:
      m1 = m2
      m2 = arr1[i]
      i += 1
    else:
      m1 = m2
      m2 = arr2[j]
      j += 1
  return (m1 + m2)/2
